Tag a single item. Generates a spec internally, then applies it.

#### `mapTags(list, instructions, vocabulary, config)`
Tag multiple items in batches using the `map` chain.

#### `tagSpec(instructions, config)`
Generate a reusable tagging specification. Returns `Promise<string>`.

#### `applyTags(item, specification, vocabulary, config)`
Apply a pre-generated specification with vocabulary to a single item. Returns `Promise<Array>` of tag IDs.

#### `createTagger(vocabulary, config)`
Create a vocabulary-bound tagger for consistent categorization. Returns a function `(items, instructions) => Promise<Array>` that handles both single items and arrays.

Also exposes `.mapWithVocabulary(list, overrideVocabulary?)` for direct batch tagging with optional vocabulary override.

